 to Close Out Spring Schedule in Wheeling Against Ohio State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/volleyball-mountaineers-to-close-out-spring-schedule-in-wheeling-against-ohio-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/volleyball-mountaineers-to-close-out-spring-schedule-in-wheeling-against-ohio-state</guid><category>Volleyball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="VB Team huddle" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/1/VBvsKANSAS_147__1_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University volleyball team will conclude its spring schedule with a match against Ohio State on Sunday, April 19, in Wheeling, West Virginia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/VBvsKANSAS_147__1_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/VBvsKANSAS_147__1_.jpg"><media:title>VB Team huddle</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/VBvsKANSAS_147__1_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 1 Apr 2026 12:54:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>17</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58948</s:story_id></item><item><title>Five Mountaineers Named Scholar All-Americans by NWCA</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/wrestling-five-mountaineers-named-scholar-all-americans-by-nwca</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/wrestling-five-mountaineers-named-scholar-all-americans-by-nwca</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2026 NWCA Scholar All-Americans" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/1/WRESTLE_NWCAALLAM_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Five Mountaineers from the West Virginia University wrestling team were named Scholar All-Americans by the National Wrestling Coaches Association (NWCA) on Wednesday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/WRESTLE_NWCAALLAM_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/WRESTLE_NWCAALLAM_1920x1080.png"><media:title>2026 NWCA Scholar All-Americans</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/WRESTLE_NWCAALLAM_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 1 Apr 2026 12:10:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58947</s:story_id></item><item><title>Kelly Named to Buster Posey Award Watch List</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-kelly-named-to-buster-posey-award-watch-list</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-kelly-named-to-buster-posey-award-watch-list</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/1/BXZ01626_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University sophomore Gavin Kelly has been named to the Buster Posey Award midseason watch list. The award is presented each year to the nation's most outstanding catcher by the Wichita Sports Commission.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/BXZ01626_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/BXZ01626_large.jpg"><media:title>Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/1/BXZ01626_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 1 Apr 2026 11:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58946</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Concludes Road Trip With Win at Arizona</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-west-virginia-concludes-road-trip-with-win-at-arizona</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-west-virginia-concludes-road-trip-with-win-at-arizona</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Carson Estridge" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" /><br /><br />TUCSON, Ariz. – The No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Arizona, 7-4, Tuesday night in a non-conference game at Hi Corbett Field. The Mountaineers improve to 20-5 while the Wildcats fall to 9-19.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg"><media:title>Carson Estridge</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 1 Apr 2026 02:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58944</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Set to Play at Arizona</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-play-at-arizona</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-play-at-arizona</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup at Arizona" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team caps off its trip to the Valley of the Sun with a midweek non-conference game on March 31, against Arizona. First pitch from Hi Corbett Field in Tucson is set for 9 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg"><media:title>Matchup at Arizona</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 17:48:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58942</s:story_id></item><item><title>McDonald Named Student-Athlete of the Week</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/track-field-mcdonald-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/track-field-mcdonald-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Annishka McDonald @ Raliegh Relays" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Redshirt junior Annishka McDonald of the West Virginia University track and field team has been named the WVU Student-Athlete of the Week, presented by University Apartments.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg"><media:title>Annishka McDonald @ Raliegh Relays</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 11:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58941</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Claim Series From No. 22 Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-mountaineers-claim-series-from-no-22-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-mountaineers-claim-series-from-no-22-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team earned a ranked Big 12 series win on Sunday night with a 9-5 victory over No. 22 Arizona State in front on a national TV audience. The Mountaineers improve to 19-5 and 7-2 in the Big 12 while the Sun Devils fall to 20-8 and 5-4 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg"><media:title>Chansen Cole, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:50:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58940</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Even Series Against No. 22 Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/29/baseball-mountaineers-even-series-against-no-22-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/29/baseball-mountaineers-even-series-against-no-22-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team defeated No. 22 Arizona State, 13-7, Saturday night at Phoenix Municipal Stadium to even up the series at a game apiece. The Mountaineers improve to 18-5 overall and 6-2 in the Big 12 while the Sun Devils fall to 20-7 and 5-3 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 02:28:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58939</s:story_id></item><item><title>McDonald Sets Outdoor School Record at Raleigh Relays</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/track-field-mcdonald-sets-outdoor-school-record-at-raleigh-relays</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/track-field-mcdonald-sets-outdoor-school-record-at-raleigh-relays</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Annishka McDonald" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Annishka McDonald highlighted West Virginia's weekend at the Raleigh Relays, setting a new outdoor school record in the high jump.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png"><media:title>Annishka McDonald</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 28 Mar 2026 22:06:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58938</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>